WEBVTT

00:00:00.380 --> 00:00:01.540
Good day.

00:00:01.820 --> 00:00:04.260
My name is Natalya Ivanovna Dmitrieva.

00:00:04.270 --> 00:00:06.400
The World Trade Organization

00:00:06.410 --> 00:00:08.500
changes the Russian

00:00:08.510 --> 00:00:10.320
economy.

00:00:10.900 --> 00:00:12.360
In the course of international

00:00:12.370 --> 00:00:13.720
economic relations we considered

00:00:13.730 --> 00:00:17.340
with you that one of the forms

00:00:17.350 --> 00:00:18.960
of international economic relations

00:00:18.970 --> 00:00:21.260
is interstate

00:00:21.270 --> 00:00:24.080
regulation of foreign

00:00:24.090 --> 00:00:25.740
trade relations.

00:00:26.460 --> 00:00:28.140
The organizations involved in this process

00:00:28.150 --> 00:00:29.720
are, first of all, the International

00:00:29.730 --> 00:00:31.060
Monetary Fund, the World Bank,

00:00:31.140 --> 00:00:35.040
the Bank for International Settlements.

00:00:35.380 --> 00:00:37.540
The World Trade Organization is one

00:00:37.550 --> 00:00:40.100
of the international organizations

00:00:40.110 --> 00:00:44.100
that regulates foreign economic

00:00:44.110 --> 00:00:48.500
relations within the framework

00:00:48.510 --> 00:00:52.480
of the activities of about 150 countries.

00:00:53.040 --> 00:00:55.000
The World Trade Organization

00:00:55.010 --> 00:00:57.740
(WTO) is the first organization

00:00:57.750 --> 00:01:00.560
that regulates trade relations.

00:01:00.780 --> 00:01:03.000
The history of the establishment

00:01:03.010 --> 00:01:04.960
of the World Trade Organization.

00:01:05.760 --> 00:01:09.240
In the postwar period of 47 years,

00:01:09.250 --> 00:01:13.220
as we already know, the countries

00:01:13.230 --> 00:01:16.380
of Europe were moving to remove

00:01:16.390 --> 00:01:19.020
barriers, because in the postwar

00:01:19.030 --> 00:01:21.500
period the barriers were so

00:01:21.510 --> 00:01:25.460
high that they were essentially prohibitive.

00:01:27.460 --> 00:01:30.080
The assistance of the United States of America

00:01:30.090 --> 00:01:33.560
under the Marshal Plan envisaged the

00:01:33.570 --> 00:01:35.840
fulfillment by all countries of

00:01:35.850 --> 00:01:38.280
the future European Union of the

00:01:38.290 --> 00:01:40.300
conditions of liberalization

00:01:40.310 --> 00:01:42.060
of foreign trade relations.

00:01:42.580 --> 00:01:45.520
Therefore, negotiations within

00:01:45.530 --> 00:01:49.280
the ministries of countries that would

00:01:49.290 --> 00:01:50.700
like to liberalize their

00:01:50.710 --> 00:01:53.580
international relations began almost

00:01:53.590 --> 00:01:57.980
immediately in the post-war period.

00:01:58.580 --> 00:02:00.320
We talked for a long time,

00:02:00.330 --> 00:02:04.700
as you and I know, there

00:02:04.820 --> 00:02:06.880
were a lot of rounds.

00:02:07.180 --> 00:02:09.900
Each round lasted for more than

00:02:10.680 --> 00:02:12.740
a year, but the General

00:02:12.750 --> 00:02:15.520
Trade Tariff Agreement

00:02:15.530 --> 00:02:17.500
was eventually signed.

00:02:18.500 --> 00:02:21.020
The agreements that were reached

00:02:21.030 --> 00:02:23.220
and signed within the framework of

00:02:23.230 --> 00:02:26.180
the GATT then formed the basis

00:02:26.190 --> 00:02:28.620
for the next stage of development

00:02:28.630 --> 00:02:29.880
of international regulation of

00:02:29.890 --> 00:02:32.740
foreign trade, namely the creation

00:02:32.750 --> 00:02:35.700
of the World Trade Organization.

00:02:36.220 --> 00:02:40.680
On January 1, 1995, the GATT

00:02:40.690 --> 00:02:42.480
was transformed into the

00:02:42.490 --> 00:02:44.520
World Trade Organization.

00:02:46.960 --> 00:02:49.020
In this case, as far as the

00:02:49.030 --> 00:02:51.600
Uruguayan documents signed as

00:02:51.610 --> 00:02:53.540
part of the Uruguayan Round, as

00:02:53.550 --> 00:02:56.700
you can see on the slide that

00:02:56.900 --> 00:02:59.600
took place from 1986 until 1994,

00:02:59.610 --> 00:03:04.280
they were the basis of the

00:03:04.290 --> 00:03:06.560
World Trade Organization.

00:03:07.040 --> 00:03:09.980
At present, the WTO membership is

00:03:09.990 --> 00:03:13.200
already 150 countries, which shows

00:03:13.210 --> 00:03:15.760
the interest of all the countries in

00:03:15.770 --> 00:03:18.060
the world, which maintain active

00:03:18.070 --> 00:03:20.140
foreign trade relations, to be included

00:03:20.280 --> 00:03:22.400
in the negotiation processes

00:03:22.410 --> 00:03:25.080
and interest in participation

00:03:25.090 --> 00:03:27.320
in the World Trade Organization.

00:03:29.120 --> 00:03:31.380
Most of the WTO member

00:03:31.390 --> 00:03:33.120
countries were members of

00:03:33.240 --> 00:03:34.760
the General Trade Tariff

00:03:34.770 --> 00:03:37.940
Agreement, but a certain

00:03:37.950 --> 00:03:39.920
number of countries joined

00:03:39.930 --> 00:03:42.800
it quite late.

00:03:43.040 --> 00:03:45.520
And if you look at the next

00:03:45.530 --> 00:03:48.100
slide, see, for example, Moldova

00:03:49.100 --> 00:03:50.760
joined the World Trade Organization

00:03:50.770 --> 00:03:52.980
in 2001, and a country

00:03:53.740 --> 00:03:55.260
like Saudi Arabia even

00:03:55.270 --> 00:03:57.520
in 2005.

00:03:58.400 --> 00:04:02.040
In this case, the processes

00:04:02.050 --> 00:04:04.720
in recent years have become more

00:04:04.730 --> 00:04:06.480
complex for many countries.

00:04:06.560 --> 00:04:06.880
Why is?

00:04:07.040 --> 00:04:08.740
Because, as you have seen from the

00:04:08.750 --> 00:04:10.460
history of the development of

00:04:10.470 --> 00:04:13.800
the World Trade Organization, negotiation

00:04:13.810 --> 00:04:16.720
processes have been going almost since

00:04:16.730 --> 00:04:18.340
1947.

00:04:18.720 --> 00:04:21.440
And of course, the major

00:04:21.450 --> 00:04:24.700
WTO members who were

00:04:24.710 --> 00:04:26.780
on the year-on-year deal made

00:04:28.590 --> 00:04:31.740
it easier for them to enter

00:04:31.750 --> 00:04:36.800
into their mutual agreements

00:04:36.810 --> 00:04:39.060
precisely because they had

00:04:39.070 --> 00:04:41.780
been negotiating for almost

00:04:41.790 --> 00:04:44.040
decades.

00:04:44.420 --> 00:04:46.700
On this basis, a paradoxical

00:04:46.710 --> 00:04:48.300
situation arises.

00:04:48.420 --> 00:04:51.100
Of course, new countries would

00:04:51.110 --> 00:04:52.480
like to join the World Trade

00:04:52.490 --> 00:04:55.240
Organization, but the WTO, as

00:04:55.250 --> 00:04:57.640
some integration association,

00:04:58.020 --> 00:04:59.220
now looks very closely

00:04:59.230 --> 00:05:01.160
at those members who claim

00:05:01.170 --> 00:05:03.060
to join the World Trade

00:05:03.070 --> 00:05:05.360
Organization and try to get

00:05:05.370 --> 00:05:09.760
certain preferences from

00:05:09.770 --> 00:05:11.820
new members in a more

00:05:11.830 --> 00:05:13.380
rigid manner.

00:05:13.840 --> 00:05:15.680
The old members, when they joined

00:05:15.690 --> 00:05:18.320
the WTO, were assumed to have reached

00:05:18.460 --> 00:05:20.940
a certain level of tariff changes

00:05:20.950 --> 00:05:24.660
and arrangements, and the

00:05:24.670 --> 00:05:27.560
requirement to the old members

00:05:27.570 --> 00:05:29.020
was to some extent even

00:05:29.030 --> 00:05:31.760
less stringent.

00:05:31.960 --> 00:05:34.280
But nevertheless, such a careful attention

00:05:34.290 --> 00:05:35.700
is understandable, there are

00:05:35.710 --> 00:05:37.100
economic and political interests

00:05:37.110 --> 00:05:38.840
in the participating countries, and they

00:05:38.850 --> 00:05:43.100
are trying to get all possible preferences

00:05:43.110 --> 00:05:46.160
from the emergence of a new country

00:05:46.180 --> 00:05:48.200
as a member of the World

00:05:48.210 --> 00:05:50.580
Trade Organization.

00:05:51.060 --> 00:05:53.160
The WTO is the permanent form

00:05:53.170 --> 00:05:54.960
of membership.

00:05:54.970 --> 00:05:56.960
This is due to the fact

00:05:56.970 --> 00:05:59.760
that the negotiation processes,

00:05:59.770 --> 00:06:02.640
WTO rounds are virtually not stopped,

00:06:02.650 --> 00:06:04.820
and as we will then look at the

00:06:04.830 --> 00:06:10.220
structure of the WTO, a permanent

00:06:12.790 --> 00:06:17.360
annual summit is provided within

00:06:17.370 --> 00:06:18.680
the framework of the World

00:06:18.690 --> 00:06:22.160
Trade Organization to sign

00:06:22.170 --> 00:06:25.980
or agree on some future agreements.

00:06:25.990 --> 00:06:27.860
In principle, eight rounds of

00:06:27.870 --> 00:06:33.160
international trade negotiations

00:06:33.170 --> 00:06:34.760
have been held since

00:06:34.770 --> 00:06:37.440
1991, and the last round, which

00:06:37.450 --> 00:06:39.380
is still in effect, is called

00:06:40.340 --> 00:06:43.000
the Millennium Round or

00:06:43.010 --> 00:06:46.000
Pre-Round, which, in general,

00:06:46.140 --> 00:06:48.520
began in 2000.

00:06:49.120 --> 00:06:51.160
The goal of the Dohrund

00:06:51.170 --> 00:06:52.440
is to liberalize trade

00:06:52.450 --> 00:06:53.960
in agricultural products.

00:06:54.320 --> 00:06:55.840
In general, this is the most painful

00:06:55.850 --> 00:06:58.160
problem associated with the activities

00:06:58.170 --> 00:07:00.380
of the members of the World

00:07:00.390 --> 00:07:01.680
Trade Organization.

00:07:01.820 --> 00:07:04.120
Until now, most of the WTO

00:07:04.130 --> 00:07:05.460
member countries have supported

00:07:05.470 --> 00:07:08.340
certain protectionist

00:07:08.740 --> 00:07:10.960
measures to protect national

00:07:10.970 --> 00:07:13.320
agricultural producers,

00:07:13.330 --> 00:07:14.480
believing that their

00:07:14.490 --> 00:07:18.140
production conditions are

00:07:18.150 --> 00:07:20.860
so, so to say, difficult that

00:07:20.870 --> 00:07:23.560
the state is obliged

00:07:23.570 --> 00:07:25.080
to support them and

00:07:25.090 --> 00:07:26.740
stimulate the development

00:07:26.750 --> 00:07:28.120
of domestic agricultural

00:07:28.130 --> 00:07:30.080
production.

00:07:31.140 --> 00:07:33.160
A study conducted by the World

00:07:33.170 --> 00:07:37.300
Bank in the late 1990s on the

00:07:37.310 --> 00:07:39.300
liberalization model, so

00:07:39.310 --> 00:07:42.400
to speak, showed that if possible,

00:07:42.410 --> 00:07:45.060
of course, there are three

00:07:45.070 --> 00:07:46.820
variants.

00:07:47.400 --> 00:07:48.720
The first option is such a general

00:07:48.730 --> 00:07:50.420
and complete liberalization

00:07:50.430 --> 00:07:52.540
of international economic relations.

00:07:53.160 --> 00:07:56.000
The second option is an intermediate

00:07:56.010 --> 00:07:57.220
option, when, so to speak,

00:07:57.280 --> 00:07:59.040
liberalization will reach some

00:07:59.050 --> 00:08:00.560
such average level.

00:08:00.740 --> 00:08:02.460
So, under the forecast

00:08:02.470 --> 00:08:04.760
of specialists, if the

00:08:04.770 --> 00:08:06.940
pig farm barriers are removed,

00:08:06.950 --> 00:08:08.580
then the developing countries,

00:08:08.590 --> 00:08:10.540
including new market economies,

00:08:10.550 --> 00:08:12.900
I mean Russia, are the

00:08:12.910 --> 00:08:13.900
winners.

00:08:14.600 --> 00:08:17.280
From this, it is clear what

00:08:17.290 --> 00:08:20.760
serious interests are facing

00:08:20.770 --> 00:08:21.500
within the problems

00:08:21.510 --> 00:08:23.980
of pig liberalization.

00:08:23.990 --> 00:08:27.000
These are European

00:08:27.220 --> 00:08:29.820
producers, as the European

00:08:29.830 --> 00:08:32.620
Union is known to spend

00:08:32.630 --> 00:08:34.820
50% of its EU budget

00:08:34.830 --> 00:08:35.740
on supporting

00:08:35.750 --> 00:08:37.660
its pig farmers.

00:08:38.180 --> 00:08:41.740
At the same time, the United States, walking

00:08:41.750 --> 00:08:44.760
and accusing Europe of direct protectionism

00:08:44.770 --> 00:08:47.260
in supporting its

00:08:47.270 --> 00:08:49.260
agricultural experience.

00:08:49.270 --> 00:08:53.020
Nevertheless, the United States also

00:08:53.030 --> 00:08:55.600
in the late 1990s carried out an intra-

00:08:55.610 --> 00:08:58.440
national program for modernizing

00:09:00.130 --> 00:09:01.740
agriculture, to stimulate

00:09:01.750 --> 00:09:04.480
the intensification of production.

00:09:04.700 --> 00:09:07.280
And accordingly, within this program

00:09:07.290 --> 00:09:09.920
there were also options for financial

00:09:16.050 --> 00:09:18.960
support of the organization.

00:09:19.660 --> 00:09:21.800
The main goal of the agreement

00:09:21.810 --> 00:09:23.600
is to further liberalize

00:09:23.610 --> 00:09:26.960
world trade and ensure

00:09:26.970 --> 00:09:29.260
fair competition.

00:09:29.580 --> 00:09:32.160
As we discussed with you in the course

00:09:32.170 --> 00:09:33.800
of international economic relations,

00:09:33.810 --> 00:09:37.900
the principle that the second best

00:09:37.910 --> 00:09:39.960
is not given, namely, better than

00:09:40.280 --> 00:09:41.640
liberal economic relations, which

00:09:41.650 --> 00:09:44.720
involve the rapid development

00:09:44.730 --> 00:09:47.900
of export relations, has not

00:09:47.980 --> 00:09:49.940
yet been invented by mankind.

00:09:50.280 --> 00:09:52.360
Another thing is that at some stage

00:09:52.370 --> 00:09:54.780
of its development, each country

00:09:54.790 --> 00:09:56.860
defends its national interests,

00:09:56.870 --> 00:10:00.360
considers the situation that

00:10:00.380 --> 00:10:01.580
develops in the national

00:10:01.590 --> 00:10:03.640
economy, and within the economic

00:10:03.650 --> 00:10:06.300
cycle, if there is a situation

00:10:06.310 --> 00:10:08.260
of recession, crisis or

00:10:08.360 --> 00:10:10.460
some threat, in particular

00:10:10.470 --> 00:10:12.940
to agriculture, then it

00:10:12.950 --> 00:10:15.120
tries to protect its national

00:10:15.130 --> 00:10:16.680
producers.

00:10:17.620 --> 00:10:20.840
Therefore, the national interests

00:10:20.850 --> 00:10:22.980
of some individual countries may

00:10:22.990 --> 00:10:26.040
go against the interests of

00:10:26.050 --> 00:10:27.960
the world community, which is

00:10:28.120 --> 00:10:29.980
interested in the general liberalization

00:10:29.990 --> 00:10:31.140
of international trade,

00:10:31.150 --> 00:10:33.980
as such will lead to a more rational

00:10:33.990 --> 00:10:35.660
redistribution of

00:10:35.670 --> 00:10:37.640
resources in the world, their

00:10:37.650 --> 00:10:40.360
effective use, and, consequently,

00:10:40.370 --> 00:10:41.960
will lead to the growth

00:10:42.080 --> 00:10:46.720
of the world gross product.

00:10:47.220 --> 00:10:50.060
What are the specific goals of the

00:10:50.070 --> 00:10:51.300
World Trade Organization?

00:10:51.380 --> 00:10:54.460
First of all, they aim to

00:10:54.740 --> 00:10:56.920
support existing agreements,

00:10:56.930 --> 00:11:00.340
track them, and, so to

00:11:00.350 --> 00:11:01.500
speak, live.

00:11:09.380 --> 00:11:11.760
Namely, the agreements on trade in

00:11:11.770 --> 00:11:14.860
services and agreements that have

00:11:14.870 --> 00:11:16.480
been signed in the last decade,

00:11:16.490 --> 00:11:18.880
almost the decade of

00:11:18.890 --> 00:11:21.400
the twentieth century.

00:11:21.600 --> 00:11:24.260
This is practically an agreement

00:11:24.270 --> 00:11:26.720
within the WTO, not within,

00:11:26.730 --> 00:11:28.320
so to speak, the GAD.

00:11:28.500 --> 00:11:32.440
This is the TRIMS agreement, which bears the name.

00:11:32.600 --> 00:11:34.840
This is the agreement on trade

00:11:34.850 --> 00:11:37.500
aspects of the transfer of intellectual

00:11:37.510 --> 00:11:40.440
property rights and the TRIMS

00:11:40.450 --> 00:11:44.340
agreement, that is, an

00:11:44.350 --> 00:11:45.880
agreement between countries

00:11:46.020 --> 00:11:48.120
on trade aspects of investment

00:11:48.130 --> 00:11:49.540
measures.

00:11:50.520 --> 00:11:53.000
Of course, the current goal,

00:11:53.010 --> 00:11:56.080
as I said, within the Doharound

00:11:56.090 --> 00:11:59.360
is to create a new agreement

00:11:59.370 --> 00:12:01.680
on retail products.

00:12:03.980 --> 00:12:07.400
What are the basic principles of GAD?

00:12:11.540 --> 00:12:14.240
First of all, it is assumed that

00:12:14.250 --> 00:12:16.540
it is within this agreement that

00:12:16.550 --> 00:12:20.740
the regime of the greatest favor

00:12:20.750 --> 00:12:22.720
works most adequately.

00:12:23.400 --> 00:12:25.660
What is his main idea?

00:12:25.670 --> 00:12:29.020
It is assumed that the member countries, when

00:12:29.260 --> 00:12:30.800
arranging foreign trade relations,

00:12:30.810 --> 00:12:33.220
are oriented to the fact that the conditions

00:12:35.440 --> 00:12:38.240
of trade between the countries

00:12:38.250 --> 00:12:40.280
will be no worse than the conditions

00:12:40.290 --> 00:12:42.760
between other member countries.

00:12:42.820 --> 00:12:45.440
Thus, it is assumed that the countries will

00:12:45.450 --> 00:12:49.300
not increase the tariffs that have already

00:12:49.310 --> 00:12:53.440
been introduced between the other member countries.

00:12:53.480 --> 00:12:55.240
That is, in essence, it is

00:12:55.250 --> 00:12:57.180
an agreement on a certain level

00:12:57.190 --> 00:12:59.140
of protectionist protection.

00:12:59.500 --> 00:13:02.220
The next principle of the General

00:13:02.230 --> 00:13:06.900
Agreement on Trade and Tariffs is

00:13:06.910 --> 00:13:08.600
the mutual granting of national

00:13:08.610 --> 00:13:10.900
treatment.

00:13:10.910 --> 00:13:12.520
What is meant here?

00:13:12.960 --> 00:13:16.480
In this case, the main purpose

00:13:16.490 --> 00:13:20.840
of this agreement is to create a

00:13:20.850 --> 00:13:22.640
situation in which the importer

00:13:22.650 --> 00:13:30.700
would have on its own producers,

00:13:30.710 --> 00:13:32.280
that is, it would be granted

00:13:32.290 --> 00:13:34.620
the same rights as its producers,

00:13:34.660 --> 00:13:36.760
which would increase competition

00:13:36.770 --> 00:13:38.640
for national producers

00:13:38.800 --> 00:13:40.860
and from the point of

00:13:40.870 --> 00:13:42.800
view of general economic

00:13:42.810 --> 00:13:45.400
theory would increase the

00:13:45.410 --> 00:13:47.080
overall efficiency

00:13:50.750 --> 00:13:53.320
of these national producers.

00:13:53.330 --> 00:13:56.000
The next principle of the GAD

00:13:56.010 --> 00:13:58.480
is regulation of trade

00:13:58.490 --> 00:14:00.760
primarily by tariff methods.

00:14:01.300 --> 00:14:03.580
We have again understood that

00:14:03.590 --> 00:14:05.660
in the framework of state

00:14:05.670 --> 00:14:06.900
regulation of foreign trade,

00:14:06.910 --> 00:14:08.780
various methods are used,

00:14:08.790 --> 00:14:11.200
and one of the most rigid

00:14:11.210 --> 00:14:13.960
methods that generally reduces

00:14:13.970 --> 00:14:16.260
the income of the state,

00:14:16.270 --> 00:14:18.140
and most importantly, tightly

00:14:18.560 --> 00:14:20.000
block the trade flows,

00:14:20.010 --> 00:14:22.280
is quota, that is, physical

00:14:22.520 --> 00:14:24.920
restriction of exports.

00:14:25.520 --> 00:14:28.140
In contrast, tariff methods allow countries

00:14:28.150 --> 00:14:31.440
- exporters, producers - exporters

00:14:31.480 --> 00:14:34.480
themselves to choose the situation,

00:14:34.490 --> 00:14:37.520
whether they want to import goods

00:14:37.530 --> 00:14:39.760
to this country under such tariffs

00:14:39.770 --> 00:14:41.980
and restrictions or not.

00:14:42.320 --> 00:14:44.100
In particular, if it is large

00:14:44.110 --> 00:14:45.580
enough firms that are

00:14:45.590 --> 00:14:47.760
interested in seizing

00:14:47.770 --> 00:14:50.480
the national local market, they

00:14:50.490 --> 00:14:53.280
will go on to pay even higher

00:14:53.290 --> 00:14:55.760
tariffs, and protectionism

00:14:55.770 --> 00:14:58.240
in this case will not have

00:14:58.250 --> 00:14:59.840
such a force.

00:14:59.880 --> 00:15:02.040
That is, the level of the real rate

00:15:02.050 --> 00:15:03.780
of tariff protection will be much

00:15:03.790 --> 00:15:05.940
lower, precisely because these

00:15:05.950 --> 00:15:08.540
large exporters for such market

00:15:08.550 --> 00:15:10.560
penetration can slightly reduce

00:15:10.570 --> 00:15:13.820
their entry prices.

00:15:13.900 --> 00:15:16.420
Then in this case, the price will

00:15:16.430 --> 00:15:19.060
not rise in the domestic market

00:15:19.070 --> 00:15:21.240
as much as it would have risen

00:15:21.250 --> 00:15:24.340
with the increase of tariffs and

00:15:24.350 --> 00:15:26.160
the absence of a drop in world

00:15:26.170 --> 00:15:26.880
prices.

00:15:27.440 --> 00:15:30.240
On the other hand, in this case,

00:15:30.320 --> 00:15:33.340
although consumers win,

00:15:33.540 --> 00:15:34.560
some producers of

00:15:34.570 --> 00:15:36.660
the national economy lose.

00:15:36.880 --> 00:15:41.040
But the main idea is that the

00:15:41.050 --> 00:15:44.240
competitiveness factor and

00:15:44.250 --> 00:15:46.620
the maintenance of the competitiveness

00:15:47.200 --> 00:15:49.760
of national producers will

00:15:49.770 --> 00:15:52.720
act, and these firms, foreign

00:15:52.880 --> 00:15:54.400
competitors, will push

00:15:54.410 --> 00:15:56.760
national producers

00:15:56.770 --> 00:16:00.560
to some measures to change

00:16:00.570 --> 00:16:02.500
their production.

00:16:02.510 --> 00:16:04.960
This factor is positive.

00:16:06.020 --> 00:16:09.520
The following principle of

00:16:09.530 --> 00:16:12.080
GAD is related to the refusal

00:16:12.090 --> 00:16:14.300
to use quantitative restrictions.

00:16:14.860 --> 00:16:16.620
The quantitative restrictions

00:16:16.630 --> 00:16:18.040
in this case, I will remind

00:16:18.340 --> 00:16:20.480
you, include not only quotas,

00:16:20.490 --> 00:16:22.720
but rather strict licensing and,

00:16:22.730 --> 00:16:25.540
accordingly, various measures

00:16:25.620 --> 00:16:27.280
associated with the distribution

00:16:27.290 --> 00:16:29.600
of these licenses, often

00:16:31.470 --> 00:16:33.620
not on a competitive basis,

00:16:33.630 --> 00:16:37.940
on the basis of the decision

00:16:37.950 --> 00:16:40.260
of any government officials.

00:16:41.000 --> 00:16:42.560
In this case, the abandonment

00:16:42.570 --> 00:16:44.100
of quantitative restrictions

00:16:44.110 --> 00:16:47.080
means a world that is acting to

00:16:47.090 --> 00:16:48.900
increase transparency of

00:16:48.910 --> 00:16:50.860
the country’s economic policy,

00:16:51.140 --> 00:16:53.400
insofar as, as I have said, the

00:16:53.410 --> 00:16:55.000
decision to give license to some

00:16:55.010 --> 00:16:56.880
officials or not to give, contributes

00:16:56.890 --> 00:16:59.660
to the rent-oriented behavior

00:16:59.670 --> 00:17:00.880
of politicians, and, therefore,

00:17:00.890 --> 00:17:03.140
the possibility of developing

00:17:04.360 --> 00:17:05.980
corrupt relations

00:17:05.990 --> 00:17:07.420
that will undoubtedly

00:17:07.440 --> 00:17:08.760
undermine international

00:17:08.770 --> 00:17:11.580
competition.

00:17:12.060 --> 00:17:14.360
The next principle that is related

00:17:14.370 --> 00:17:16.140
to the activities of

00:17:16.150 --> 00:17:17.920
the General Agreement on Tariffs

00:17:17.930 --> 00:17:21.220
and Trade is the transparency

00:17:21.230 --> 00:17:23.940
or transparency of trade policy.

00:17:23.950 --> 00:17:26.120
It is, of course, related to the fact

00:17:26.130 --> 00:17:29.040
that if countries decide, first,

00:17:29.050 --> 00:17:30.920
to limit quantitative restrictions,

00:17:30.930 --> 00:17:32.320
develop a policy that will

00:17:33.040 --> 00:17:34.760
be understandable to both countries,

00:17:34.770 --> 00:17:37.520
both the exporter and the importer,

00:17:37.530 --> 00:17:39.800
will reduce the risk factor

00:17:40.080 --> 00:17:42.640
that arises in connection

00:17:42.650 --> 00:17:43.880
with the inefficiency

00:17:43.890 --> 00:17:46.440
of policy in decision-making

00:17:46.450 --> 00:17:52.320
by somehow reducing opacity

00:17:53.200 --> 00:17:55.280
of economic activity,

00:17:55.290 --> 00:17:56.640
will contribute to

00:17:56.720 --> 00:17:58.660
the development of international

00:17:58.670 --> 00:18:01.520
foreign trade.

00:18:02.540 --> 00:18:04.500
The last principle I would like to

00:18:04.510 --> 00:18:06.660
draw your attention to is the settlement

00:18:07.100 --> 00:18:09.820
of trade disputes through consultation,

00:18:09.830 --> 00:18:11.900
first and foremost, and negotiations.

00:18:12.120 --> 00:18:13.000


00:18:13.460 --> 00:18:16.120
This system, which exists within the

00:18:16.130 --> 00:18:17.940
framework of the General Agreement

00:18:17.950 --> 00:18:20.120
on Trade Tariffs, attracts

00:18:20.130 --> 00:18:22.860
many countries, as it is sufficiently

00:18:22.870 --> 00:18:25.780
effective and there are

00:18:25.790 --> 00:18:28.360
many appeals from member

00:18:28.370 --> 00:18:32.180
countries to resolve trade disputes.

00:18:33.700 --> 00:18:35.660
What are the main functions of the World

00:18:35.670 --> 00:18:37.340
Trade Organization?

00:18:38.320 --> 00:18:39.920
The first function is, of course,

00:18:40.000 --> 00:18:42.040
the function of monitoring the

00:18:42.050 --> 00:18:44.400
implementation of those agreements

00:18:44.410 --> 00:18:46.580
that have already been reached

00:18:46.590 --> 00:18:48.880
within the WTO.

00:18:49.300 --> 00:18:52.040
The second direction, functional

00:18:52.050 --> 00:18:55.640
WTO, is to conduct multilateral

00:18:55.650 --> 00:18:58.140
trade negotiations in order

00:18:58.300 --> 00:18:59.680
to eventually make further

00:18:59.690 --> 00:19:01.060
decisions on liberalizing

00:19:01.070 --> 00:19:02.460
international economic

00:19:02.470 --> 00:19:04.000
relations.

00:19:04.780 --> 00:19:06.680
Solution of trade disputes,

00:19:06.960 --> 00:19:09.760
of course, trade wars do

00:19:09.770 --> 00:19:11.260
not lead to improved

00:19:11.270 --> 00:19:13.740
welfare of any of the parties

00:19:13.920 --> 00:19:15.700
involved in these trade

00:19:15.710 --> 00:19:17.040
wars.

00:19:17.050 --> 00:19:19.460
Usually, the country of import and the

00:19:19.470 --> 00:19:21.520
country of export are losers.

00:19:22.440 --> 00:19:24.700
The next functional direction

00:19:24.710 --> 00:19:27.680
of the WTO is monitoring the

00:19:27.690 --> 00:19:29.760
national trade policies of the

00:19:29.770 --> 00:19:31.660
member countries.

00:19:31.920 --> 00:19:34.820
It is an interesting area, which

00:19:35.020 --> 00:19:37.680
I will discuss in more detail later.

00:19:38.000 --> 00:19:41.020
Technical assistance to

00:19:41.030 --> 00:19:43.160
developing countries for the development

00:19:43.170 --> 00:19:49.840
of export-related programs.

00:19:49.880 --> 00:19:52.960
This technical assistance

00:19:52.970 --> 00:19:56.140
is primarily for international

00:19:56.150 --> 00:19:57.980
trade.

00:19:58.480 --> 00:19:59.940
The next direction is cooperation

00:19:59.950 --> 00:20:01.580
with international specialized

00:20:01.590 --> 00:20:04.320
organizations, both within

00:20:04.330 --> 00:20:06.600
the WTO and those subdivisions

00:20:06.610 --> 00:20:10.840
that are related to the

00:20:10.850 --> 00:20:15.340
UN, the United Nations.

00:20:15.460 --> 00:20:17.080
What are the main advantages of WTO

00:20:17.090 --> 00:20:19.200
membership?

00:20:20.160 --> 00:20:22.140
First of all, such fundamental advantages

00:20:22.150 --> 00:20:25.500
can be highlighted here.

00:20:25.720 --> 00:20:28.060
First, relations between countries

00:20:28.070 --> 00:20:32.100
members of the WTO are more predictable.

00:20:32.360 --> 00:20:32.500
Why is?

00:20:32.700 --> 00:20:34.300
Because it is assumed that

00:20:34.310 --> 00:20:36.640
before signing an agreement within

00:20:36.650 --> 00:20:39.060
the WTO, all parties that

00:20:39.070 --> 00:20:41.800
are interested in this,

00:20:41.810 --> 00:20:42.920
so to speak, signing

00:20:42.930 --> 00:20:44.420
this agreement, they

00:20:44.430 --> 00:20:45.640
must consult.

00:20:46.140 --> 00:20:47.680
This does not mean that

00:20:47.690 --> 00:20:51.860
all 150 WTO member countries

00:20:51.870 --> 00:20:55.000
will sign the agreement

00:20:55.010 --> 00:20:56.880
with each other.

00:20:56.920 --> 00:20:58.720
It is assumed that from this group

00:20:58.730 --> 00:21:00.700
will simply stand out, for example,

00:21:00.710 --> 00:21:02.460
a group of countries that

00:21:02.470 --> 00:21:05.580
are interested in the aspect

00:21:05.840 --> 00:21:07.700
that is being developed at

00:21:07.710 --> 00:21:08.480
this time.

00:21:08.800 --> 00:21:10.180
For example, let’s take the

00:21:10.640 --> 00:21:12.340
agreement on the liberalization

00:21:12.350 --> 00:21:14.440
of agricultural products.

00:21:14.520 --> 00:21:17.080
Not all 150 countries, but

00:21:17.460 --> 00:21:18.800
those that are exporting

00:21:18.810 --> 00:21:20.680
or importing agricultural

00:21:20.690 --> 00:21:22.240
products, will take

00:21:22.250 --> 00:21:25.600
part in these negotiations.

00:21:25.780 --> 00:21:27.660
So, the predictability of trade relations,

00:21:27.670 --> 00:21:29.680
it is guaranteed in this case

00:21:29.690 --> 00:21:31.440
by the correct WTO

00:21:31.450 --> 00:21:33.160
prescribed.

00:21:34.260 --> 00:21:37.900
And here in this same section we need

00:21:37.910 --> 00:21:40.140
to talk about the transparency

00:21:40.150 --> 00:21:42.020
of the foreign economic policy of

00:21:42.030 --> 00:21:45.240
the member countries, which

00:21:45.420 --> 00:21:47.380
is supported by various WTO

00:21:47.390 --> 00:21:50.160
activities, in particular, by

00:21:50.220 --> 00:21:52.660
the analysis of foreign trade policy,

00:21:52.670 --> 00:21:55.460
which is regularly conducted

00:21:55.470 --> 00:21:58.560
for one country or another.

00:21:58.660 --> 00:22:00.180
Eliminating discrimination

00:22:00.190 --> 00:22:02.080
in trade is also an advantage, since

00:22:02.560 --> 00:22:04.940
the principle of non-discrimination

00:22:04.950 --> 00:22:07.060
is the second fundamental principle

00:22:07.070 --> 00:22:08.320
of a trade organisation,

00:22:08.330 --> 00:22:10.240
which implies that unreasonable

00:22:11.380 --> 00:22:13.600
discriminatory measures cannot

00:22:13.610 --> 00:22:15.920
be applied against

00:22:15.930 --> 00:22:17.480
a member country.

00:22:19.150 --> 00:22:21.810
Access to the WTO Dispute Resolution

00:22:21.820 --> 00:22:23.090
Mechanism.

00:22:25.010 --> 00:22:29.530
This advantage is to be obtained

00:22:29.540 --> 00:22:31.510
by all those countries that at

00:22:31.520 --> 00:22:34.570
this stage of time are trying

00:22:34.580 --> 00:22:38.190
to enter the WTO and are negotiating

00:22:38.200 --> 00:22:40.910
the entry of the all-rounder

00:22:40.920 --> 00:22:42.990
trade organization.

00:22:44.410 --> 00:22:47.190
And the last advantage, which can be

00:22:47.200 --> 00:22:49.890
called in the category of the main,

00:22:50.550 --> 00:22:53.910
is the participation in the development

00:22:53.920 --> 00:22:55.790
of these agreements, that is, participation

00:22:55.800 --> 00:22:59.490
in international trade negotiations.

00:22:59.850 --> 00:23:03.150
Of course, a WTO member has a greater right

00:23:03.160 --> 00:23:06.190
of voice, it is easier to hear than

00:23:06.370 --> 00:23:09.350
an outsider from this organization.

00:23:10.910 --> 00:23:12.190
What is the legal basis

00:23:12.200 --> 00:23:14.150
of a trade organization?

00:23:15.250 --> 00:23:17.350
The WTO system could be called a multilateral

00:23:17.360 --> 00:23:19.930
contract that involves the signing

00:23:19.940 --> 00:23:22.550
of a whole package of

00:23:22.560 --> 00:23:24.530
agreements.

00:23:25.310 --> 00:23:27.710
The WTO rules are practically

00:23:27.720 --> 00:23:32.550
applied to most countries, as I

00:23:32.560 --> 00:23:34.550
have said, the 150 most active

00:23:34.560 --> 00:23:35.990
trading partners, and 97

00:23:36.000 --> 00:23:39.310
percent of world trade is controlled

00:23:39.670 --> 00:23:42.610
by the World Trade

00:23:42.620 --> 00:23:44.890
Organization within the

00:23:44.900 --> 00:23:47.230
framework of these rules.

00:23:47.510 --> 00:23:50.670
The Uruguay Round, which

00:23:50.680 --> 00:23:53.370
is the basis of the WTO,

00:23:53.590 --> 00:23:55.970
has about 50 agreements.

00:23:58.520 --> 00:24:00.660
What are the principles of decision-making

00:24:00.670 --> 00:24:02.720
in the World Trade Organization?

00:24:03.440 --> 00:24:06.140
This is the consensus method.

00:24:06.560 --> 00:24:08.820
It is expected that there are

00:24:14.090 --> 00:24:17.680
very long negotiations between

00:24:17.740 --> 00:24:21.440
all interested in making this decision.

00:24:21.450 --> 00:24:25.600
It is supposed that it is better to

00:24:25.610 --> 00:24:29.060
shake down all the disputed issues,

00:24:29.070 --> 00:24:31.580
to remove them, than to leave

00:24:31.590 --> 00:24:33.560
a losing side to the very

00:24:33.570 --> 00:24:36.780
minority, which is dissatisfied

00:24:36.790 --> 00:24:38.780
and not satisfied with the decision

00:24:38.790 --> 00:24:40.220
that, suppose, the World

00:24:40.460 --> 00:24:42.500
Trade Organization will take.

00:24:43.280 --> 00:24:45.320
In principle, the

00:24:45.330 --> 00:24:47.040
WTO statute allows

00:24:47.050 --> 00:24:49.580
the use of voting

00:24:49.590 --> 00:24:51.360
method by a

00:24:51.370 --> 00:24:54.100
majority vote.

00:24:54.440 --> 00:24:55.760
But this practice has not been implemented

00:24:55.770 --> 00:24:57.580
by the World Trade Organization

00:24:57.590 --> 00:24:58.680
so far.

00:24:59.020 --> 00:25:01.940
It is the consensus method that allows

00:25:01.950 --> 00:25:04.040
to conclude such contractual

00:25:04.050 --> 00:25:06.540
relationships that are stable

00:25:06.550 --> 00:25:09.160
and that all WTO member

00:25:09.170 --> 00:25:12.520
countries are satisfied with.

00:25:15.520 --> 00:25:18.000
What is the decision-making

00:25:18.010 --> 00:25:20.740
structure within the

00:25:20.750 --> 00:25:22.760
World Trade Organization?

00:25:23.680 --> 00:25:26.620
First of all, it is a ministerial

00:25:26.630 --> 00:25:29.320
conference, which meets once

00:25:29.330 --> 00:25:30.700
every two years.

00:25:31.120 --> 00:25:33.240
The Ministerial Conference

00:25:33.250 --> 00:25:35.880
is the legislative

00:25:35.890 --> 00:25:37.840
body.

00:25:42.540 --> 00:25:44.140
Multilateral agreements,

00:25:44.150 --> 00:25:46.200
packages of agreements are being

00:25:46.210 --> 00:25:48.120
signed or negotiations are

00:25:48.130 --> 00:25:49.780
being held on some issue in order

00:25:49.790 --> 00:25:52.100
to further remove those issues

00:25:52.110 --> 00:25:54.060
that have not been resolved

00:25:54.070 --> 00:25:55.900
at the moment of the negotiation

00:25:55.910 --> 00:25:57.080
round.

00:25:57.420 --> 00:25:58.780
In this case, it is a

00:25:58.790 --> 00:26:00.440
legislative body.

00:26:00.920 --> 00:26:03.600
All the branches of the World

00:26:03.610 --> 00:26:05.840
Trade Organization are not

00:26:05.850 --> 00:26:07.860
legislative bodies, but

00:26:07.870 --> 00:26:10.140
executive, so to speak, governmental

00:26:10.150 --> 00:26:12.900
structures that help

00:26:12.910 --> 00:26:14.640
implement the decisions

00:26:14.650 --> 00:26:16.800
of the World Trade Organization.

00:26:16.810 --> 00:26:18.300


00:26:18.640 --> 00:26:20.960
The General Council is the most

00:26:20.970 --> 00:26:24.480
important executive body, usually

00:26:24.490 --> 00:26:26.760
composed of ambassadors and

00:26:26.770 --> 00:26:29.720
heads of delegations.

00:26:31.980 --> 00:26:33.900
Please look at the slide that represents

00:26:34.080 --> 00:26:36.360
the most generalized structure

00:26:36.370 --> 00:26:38.520
of the peace trade

00:26:38.530 --> 00:26:39.940
organization.

00:26:40.540 --> 00:26:43.620
The Ministerial Conference

00:26:43.640 --> 00:26:46.740
is, as we say, a legislative

00:26:46.960 --> 00:26:48.000
body.

00:26:48.010 --> 00:26:49.860
The WTO General Council as

00:26:49.870 --> 00:26:51.380
the executive body.

00:26:51.580 --> 00:26:55.160
The General Council is bound

00:26:55.170 --> 00:26:57.580
by three functional councils.

00:26:58.220 --> 00:26:59.920
It is the Council on Trade in Goods,

00:27:00.060 --> 00:27:03.200
the Council on Trade and the Council

00:27:03.210 --> 00:27:04.560
on Trade Aspects of Intellectual

00:27:04.570 --> 00:27:06.760
Property Rights.

00:27:07.340 --> 00:27:08.960
Besides the councils

00:27:08.970 --> 00:27:10.980
of such auxiliary, there are trade

00:27:10.990 --> 00:27:13.620
and development committees, budget

00:27:14.160 --> 00:27:17.440
committees, etc., which help

00:27:17.820 --> 00:27:19.780
the WTO General Council

00:27:19.790 --> 00:27:22.660
perform its administrative

00:27:22.670 --> 00:27:24.800
functions.

00:27:25.240 --> 00:27:27.520
As I said before, there is

00:27:27.530 --> 00:27:34.440
a WTO secretariat, but the secretariat

00:27:34.450 --> 00:27:38.460
does not have legislative functions

00:27:38.470 --> 00:27:40.520
and does not make decisions.

00:27:40.800 --> 00:27:42.660
This is a service body.

00:27:44.520 --> 00:27:47.880
Let us now turn to the issue

00:27:47.890 --> 00:27:50.640
of Russian foreign trade in order

00:27:50.900 --> 00:27:53.200
to finally understand why Russia

00:27:53.210 --> 00:27:55.600
needs to join the World Trade

00:27:55.610 --> 00:27:56.940
Organization.

00:27:57.380 --> 00:27:58.820
On the one hand, yes,

00:27:58.830 --> 00:27:59.940
we looked at the whole

00:27:59.950 --> 00:28:02.220
block of benefits that WTO

00:28:02.230 --> 00:28:05.260
members receive, and especially

00:28:05.420 --> 00:28:07.520
those members that have

00:28:07.530 --> 00:28:09.180
just joined the WTO.

00:28:09.460 --> 00:28:11.140
But on the other hand, as I said,

00:28:11.150 --> 00:28:13.500
there is a situation where new members

00:28:14.180 --> 00:28:18.060
are subjected to more stringent requirements

00:28:18.070 --> 00:28:20.880
than those members who were

00:28:20.890 --> 00:28:24.700
at the origin of the GAD.

00:28:25.360 --> 00:28:27.700
Accordingly, each country, before

00:28:27.710 --> 00:28:29.180
joining the World Trade Organization,

00:28:29.190 --> 00:28:31.540
must weigh all the for

00:28:31.550 --> 00:28:34.220
and against of joining

00:28:34.230 --> 00:28:36.620
the World Trade Organization.

00:28:36.900 --> 00:28:39.120
Each country should look at what

00:28:39.300 --> 00:28:41.140
concessions it can and cannot make,

00:28:41.280 --> 00:28:42.980
and what preferences it should

00:28:42.990 --> 00:28:45.240
simply demand from those

00:28:45.250 --> 00:28:48.140
countries that are members

00:28:48.150 --> 00:28:51.280
of the World Trade Organization.

