Well, if we recall the examples of new

00:58:20.970 --> 00:58:22.920
industrialized countries that have

00:58:22.930 --> 00:58:26.080
rapidly developed exports of developing

00:58:26.090 --> 00:58:28.940
industries, and not raw materials,

00:58:28.950 --> 00:58:31.020
namely industrial, then these exports

00:58:31.260 --> 00:58:34.520
developed industries, first of

00:58:34.530 --> 00:58:36.640
all, were created at the expense

00:58:36.650 --> 00:58:38.820
of foreign investments.

