Why is?

01:43:14.840 --> 01:43:16.600
Because I said before, when you and

01:43:16.610 --> 01:43:20.000
I discussed the introduction

01:43:20.010 --> 01:43:22.100
of economic sanctions, that,

01:43:22.110 --> 01:43:23.640
for example, economic sanctions

01:43:23.650 --> 01:43:26.080
are often the result of political

01:43:26.090 --> 01:43:27.560
struggle.

01:43:28.380 --> 01:43:30.980
And they themselves do not

01:43:30.990 --> 01:43:33.200
reflect any trade disputes.

01:43:33.700 --> 01:43:36.940
They are most likely just a weapon

01:43:36.950 --> 01:43:38.560
in the hands of politicians

01:43:38.570 --> 01:43:41.000
to punish one side or the other.

01:43:41.620 --> 01:43:45.480
But, nevertheless, if we do not take

01:43:45.490 --> 01:43:48.080
the options of introducing an embargo

01:43:48.090 --> 01:43:51.200
or such restrictions, then, in

01:43:51.210 --> 01:43:53.400
general, if there is a mechanism

01:43:53.410 --> 01:43:55.480
for coordinating common decisions

01:43:55.490 --> 01:43:57.480
within the WTO, then

01:43:57.490 --> 01:44:00.420
the political situation without

01:44:00.430 --> 01:44:02.520
any major economic problems becomes

01:44:02.530 --> 01:44:05.000
more transparent and more

01:44:05.010 --> 01:44:07.900
stable, without major crisis

01:44:07.910 --> 01:44:09.820
situations.

01:44:09.920 --> 01:44:13.540
The overall benefits of Russia’s accession

01:44:13.550 --> 01:44:15.780
to the World Trade Organization are

01:44:15.790 --> 01:44:17.720
not only related to Russia itself.

01:44:18.100 --> 01:44:20.080
Per that is why the WTO

01:44:20.090 --> 01:44:21.700
members agree to move the

01:44:21.710 --> 01:44:24.580
talks, because if these countries

01:44:24.590 --> 01:44:28.640
were not interested in Russia’

01:44:28.650 --> 01:44:31.120
s accession to the WTO, they

01:44:31.130 --> 01:44:33.700
would probably have countered

01:44:33.710 --> 01:44:36.420
it in every way.

01:44:37.100 --> 01:44:38.960
Therefore, the other side of the countries

01:44:38.970 --> 01:44:40.960
and members are also interested

01:44:40.970 --> 01:44:43.620
in getting access to a sufficiently

01:44:43.630 --> 01:44:45.700
large Russian market.

01:44:46.080 --> 01:44:48.720
Therefore, the relationship between

01:44:48.730 --> 01:44:50.020
countries is settled by

01:44:50.030 --> 01:44:52.200
ensuring, first of all, equal opportunities

01:44:52.210 --> 01:44:55.680
for all members, including for

01:44:55.760 --> 01:44:59.060
small countries, which, probably,

01:44:59.220 --> 01:45:01.060
if they were to speak separately

01:45:01.070 --> 01:45:03.560
in negotiations with such a

01:45:03.570 --> 01:45:06.760
giant as Russia,, would often

01:45:06.770 --> 01:45:08.200
have less chances for

01:45:08.210 --> 01:45:11.240
defending their interests.

01:45:12.240 --> 01:45:14.880
The common benefit, again, is an

01:45:15.280 --> 01:45:16.380
effective dispute resolution

01:45:16.390 --> 01:45:19.000
mechanism, a failure to take unilateral

01:45:19.010 --> 01:45:21.220
action, which ultimately these

01:45:21.230 --> 01:45:22.800
unilateral actions usually lead

01:45:22.810 --> 01:45:24.500
to a banal trade war, when

01:45:24.510 --> 01:45:27.480
both sides start to impose counter-

01:45:27.490 --> 01:45:30.000
tariffs, quotas and restrictions,

01:45:30.010 --> 01:45:31.520
and ultimately suffer

01:45:31.530 --> 01:45:33.720
both the producer and consumer,

01:45:33.730 --> 01:45:36.560
and the countries that

01:45:36.570 --> 01:45:39.180
started the trade bath,

01:45:39.190 --> 01:45:41.500
and the country that

01:45:41.510 --> 01:45:43.340
is taking only retaliatory

01:45:43.350 --> 01:45:44.520
measures.

01:45:44.740 --> 01:45:47.660
The next benefit, of course,

01:45:47.940 --> 01:45:49.400
normal development, stable development

01:45:52.270 --> 01:45:54.600
of economic relations will reduce

01:45:54.610 --> 01:45:57.760
the risks, for example, trade, international

01:45:57.820 --> 01:45:59.460
trade crises, international financial

01:45:59.600 --> 01:46:00.980
crisis, and in the end

01:46:00.990 --> 01:46:04.220
all this strengthens international

01:46:04.230 --> 01:46:06.040
stability and pushes

01:46:06.050 --> 01:46:08.580
away the possibility

01:46:08.590 --> 01:46:10.960
of such an abnormal

01:46:10.970 --> 01:46:13.620
situation as the world economic

01:46:13.630 --> 01:46:15.340
crisis.

01:46:16.260 --> 01:46:18.960
Lastly, we will emphasize once again

01:46:19.260 --> 01:46:22.040
that in this case, the risk of political

01:46:22.050 --> 01:46:25.860
conflicts is reduced for all countries.

01:46:26.080 --> 01:46:28.200
What is the history of negotiations

01:46:28.210 --> 01:46:31.160
on Russia’s accession to the

01:46:31.170 --> 01:46:33.140
World Trade Organization?

01:46:34.360 --> 01:46:38.080
In 1993, Russia filed an application

01:46:38.090 --> 01:46:40.580
for accession to the

01:46:40.590 --> 01:46:42.780
then-existent tariff and

01:46:42.790 --> 01:46:44.400
trade agreement.

01:46:45.280 --> 01:46:46.920
And then, by the decision of the

01:46:46.930 --> 01:46:49.400
GAD, a working group on accession was created.

01:46:49.920 --> 01:46:51.980
The first thing that this working

01:46:51.990 --> 01:46:54.280
group did was to study the Russian

01:46:54.290 --> 01:46:57.300
trade regime and to elaborate

01:46:57.310 --> 01:47:00.400
those questions, problems, these

01:47:00.410 --> 01:47:02.200
requirements that Russia had

01:47:02.210 --> 01:47:04.920
to fulfill in the framework

01:47:04.930 --> 01:47:06.020
of adjusting its

01:47:06.030 --> 01:47:08.720
foreign trade regulation legislation.

01:47:09.420 --> 01:47:11.680
The 93th year is still a rather difficult

01:47:11.690 --> 01:47:13.680
year in the development of Russia itself.

01:47:14.340 --> 01:47:16.720
Therefore, of course, in the first

01:47:16.730 --> 01:47:19.880
stages up to the 95th year,

01:47:19.890 --> 01:47:23.420
there was no real negotiation

01:47:23.430 --> 01:47:25.540
process, only some conditions

01:47:25.550 --> 01:47:27.360
for further decisions

01:47:27.370 --> 01:47:28.560
were developed.

01:47:29.540 --> 01:47:31.180
As I said before, since Russia primarily

01:47:31.190 --> 01:47:33.740
trade with the European Union, it

01:47:33.750 --> 01:47:36.960
is the representatives of the European

01:47:36.970 --> 01:47:40.440
Union that were entrusted with the

01:47:40.450 --> 01:47:43.840
preparation of these very requirements

01:47:43.850 --> 01:47:46.700
and conditions for Russia’

01:47:46.710 --> 01:47:48.360
s accession to the WTO.

01:47:49.660 --> 01:47:54.640
Only in 1998 began the initial

01:47:54.650 --> 01:47:58.040
offers on access to the market

01:47:58.050 --> 01:48:03.000
of goods and services and on the

01:48:03.010 --> 01:48:06.500
level of support for agriculture,

01:48:08.790 --> 01:48:12.460
from Russia and member countries.

01:48:12.470 --> 01:48:15.040


01:48:16.340 --> 01:48:19.240
These initial proposals were

01:48:19.250 --> 01:48:21.080
adjusted for quite a while,

01:48:21.090 --> 01:48:23.320
almost for two years, and in

01:48:23.330 --> 01:48:25.800
fact only from the beginning of

01:48:25.810 --> 01:48:28.020
the new millennium in 2000 all aspects

01:48:28.030 --> 01:48:30.860
of Russia’s joining the

01:48:30.870 --> 01:48:33.300
World Trade Organization

01:48:33.320 --> 01:48:35.380
were burstingly discussed,

01:48:35.390 --> 01:48:39.800
not just the problems related

01:48:39.810 --> 01:48:42.880
to the GAD and GAC agreement.

01:48:42.890 --> 01:48:44.100


01:48:44.640 --> 01:48:46.280
The current working group, which

01:48:46.290 --> 01:48:49.460
conducts, analyzes, makes decisions,

01:48:49.480 --> 01:48:51.160
analyses the problems related to

01:48:51.220 --> 01:48:53.500
Russia’s accession to the WTO, is

01:48:53.510 --> 01:48:54.820
in a state of affairs.

01:48:55.660 --> 01:48:58.680
First of all, the requirements, as

01:48:58.690 --> 01:49:00.540
in the WTO, standard requirements

01:49:00.550 --> 01:49:02.980
for all potential WTO members.

01:49:03.140 --> 01:49:04.780
This group includes, of course, not

01:49:04.790 --> 01:49:07.680
all 150 countries, not representatives

01:49:07.690 --> 01:49:12.020
of not all 150 countries in the world,

01:49:12.030 --> 01:49:14.260
namely those countries that maintain

01:49:14.270 --> 01:49:16.400
the closest foreign trade relations

01:49:16.410 --> 01:49:19.180
with a potential member, and precisely

01:49:20.140 --> 01:49:23.100
those countries that, so to speak,

01:49:23.110 --> 01:49:26.020
have some unconsensual issues

01:49:26.030 --> 01:49:32.560
in this very foreign trade.

01:49:33.340 --> 01:49:36.800
By the end of 2006, the Working

01:49:36.810 --> 01:49:42.020
Group had 58 member countries.

01:49:42.030 --> 01:49:43.300


01:49:43.780 --> 01:49:46.020
At the same time, note, the European

01:49:46.030 --> 01:49:49.420
Union was a single bloc and

01:49:49.430 --> 01:49:51.800
considered as one country, so 58

01:49:51.810 --> 01:49:54.460
countries are a large enough group

01:49:54.470 --> 01:49:56.140
of countries, which include not

01:49:56.150 --> 01:49:57.840
only developed, but also developing

01:49:57.850 --> 01:50:00.000
countries, which are interested

01:50:00.010 --> 01:50:02.120
in the Russian market or in importing

01:50:02.130 --> 01:50:07.140
Russian products or from

01:50:07.150 --> 01:50:09.120
Russian territory.

01:50:09.480 --> 01:50:13.020
In early 2007, Vietnam

01:50:13.030 --> 01:50:14.680
and Cambodia joined

01:50:14.690 --> 01:50:16.920
the negotiations.

01:50:17.440 --> 01:50:19.300
What could this be related to?

01:50:19.360 --> 01:50:21.940
First, Vietnam and Cambodia

01:50:21.950 --> 01:50:24.820
are large agricultural

01:50:24.830 --> 01:50:27.140
producers.

01:50:27.320 --> 01:50:28.960
On the other hand, Vietnam has

01:50:28.970 --> 01:50:32.500
recently tried to intercept the world

01:50:32.510 --> 01:50:36.060
factory squad from China.

01:50:36.080 --> 01:50:37.980
That is, on the territory of Vietnam,

01:50:37.990 --> 01:50:39.300
export-oriented

01:50:39.310 --> 01:50:40.900
production of enough

01:50:40.910 --> 01:50:48.620
clothing is organized, with the

01:50:48.630 --> 01:50:52.720
assembly of some final consumption goods.

01:50:53.300 --> 01:50:55.880
They joined the negotiation

01:50:55.890 --> 01:50:58.100
process in 2007 because

01:50:58.110 --> 01:50:59.940
the barrier issues to agricultural

01:50:59.950 --> 01:51:03.480
products are being

01:51:03.490 --> 01:51:05.340
resolved right now.

01:51:05.940 --> 01:51:08.100
The number of working groups

01:51:08.110 --> 01:51:10.500
that are working on

01:51:10.510 --> 01:51:13.020
Russia’s accession to

01:51:13.030 --> 01:51:16.000
the WTO is now 50 members.

01:51:16.010 --> 01:51:18.120


01:51:20.800 --> 01:51:24.400
These are 50 member countries,

01:51:24.410 --> 01:51:26.080
which are the countries that are

01:51:26.580 --> 01:51:29.260
primarily interested in regulating

01:51:29.270 --> 01:51:31.500
trade issues.

01:51:31.940 --> 01:51:33.680
In terms of access to

01:51:33.690 --> 01:51:36.380
the Russian market, the group

01:51:36.390 --> 01:51:38.300
has about 30 members.

01:51:38.560 --> 01:51:44.240
If we summarize the situation

01:51:45.460 --> 01:51:47.240
of the negotiation process

01:51:47.250 --> 01:51:50.080
now, we can highlight the

01:51:50.090 --> 01:51:52.720
following elements of this

01:51:52.730 --> 01:51:54.680
negotiation process, which

01:51:54.690 --> 01:51:56.960
took place in 2007.

01:51:58.360 --> 01:52:00.600
First of all, it is currently determined

01:52:00.610 --> 01:52:03.040
the level of binding of

01:52:03.160 --> 01:52:06.460
the rates of roaming duties on

01:52:06.470 --> 01:52:07.860
Russian territory.

01:52:07.900 --> 01:52:09.480
What is the level of connection?

01:52:09.560 --> 01:52:11.920
It is defined by different commodity

01:52:11.930 --> 01:52:13.260
groups.

01:52:13.270 --> 01:52:15.860
The maximum interest rate

01:52:15.870 --> 01:52:19.400
that will beined after Russia

01:52:19.410 --> 01:52:20.980
joins the World

01:52:20.990 --> 01:52:22.980
Trade Organization.

01:52:23.080 --> 01:52:25.640
So, fortunately, this process is basically

01:52:25.650 --> 01:52:28.600
completed with all the members of the

01:52:28.610 --> 01:52:30.740
working group.

01:52:31.580 --> 01:52:34.100
They agreed that the initial level

01:52:34.110 --> 01:52:35.660
of bonding of customs duties

01:52:35.670 --> 01:52:39.840
would not be lower than the current level.

01:52:40.200 --> 01:52:42.280
In the first year,

01:52:42.290 --> 01:52:44.100
no tariffs will be

01:52:44.110 --> 01:52:45.060
reduced.

01:52:46.200 --> 01:52:47.880
The level of customs protection

01:52:47.890 --> 01:52:50.120
of agriculture will not decrease,

01:52:50.680 --> 01:52:53.960
and in a number of positions

01:52:53.970 --> 01:52:56.420
Russia even has the right to raise

01:52:56.430 --> 01:52:59.300
the tariffs a bit in this very

01:52:59.310 --> 01:53:02.840
transitional period until 2009.

01:53:02.960 --> 01:53:08.780
In 2009, the right to use tariff

01:53:08.790 --> 01:53:12.180
quotas for three types of meat was

01:53:12.190 --> 01:53:14.360
recorded - beef, pork and poultry

01:53:14.370 --> 01:53:15.320
meat.

01:53:17.180 --> 01:53:20.900
The technology for determining these

01:53:20.910 --> 01:53:23.700
quotas is the current level of quotas

01:53:23.710 --> 01:53:26.820
plus two and a half expansions

01:53:27.240 --> 01:53:30.900
of quotas depending on the annual

01:53:30.910 --> 01:53:35.000
growth of the supply of

01:53:35.010 --> 01:53:39.180
meat production on Russian territory.

01:53:39.960 --> 01:53:43.800
You know that 2006-2007 was marked by

01:53:43.810 --> 01:53:48.020
quite bitter disputes of the European Union,

01:53:48.030 --> 01:53:50.640
in particular Poland, over the embargo

01:53:50.650 --> 01:53:52.920
on the import of meat from the

01:53:52.930 --> 01:53:56.580
territory of the European Union, and

01:53:56.590 --> 01:53:58.680
not only from the territory of

01:53:58.690 --> 01:54:00.280
Poland, but this list includes

01:54:00.290 --> 01:54:02.060
a number of countries.

01:54:02.380 --> 01:54:06.320
It is because of the fact that, in the opinion

01:54:06.330 --> 01:54:07.900
of the Russian country, certain

01:54:07.910 --> 01:54:10.580
technical, so to speak, medical

01:54:10.590 --> 01:54:14.120
standards have been violated.

01:54:15.080 --> 01:54:18.900
In the future, as you can see, Russia

01:54:18.910 --> 01:54:21.020
has at least at this stage of negotiations

01:54:21.030 --> 01:54:23.840
obtained the right to maintain

01:54:23.850 --> 01:54:25.440
such protectionist

01:54:25.450 --> 01:54:28.100
measures with regard to meat

01:54:28.110 --> 01:54:30.240
imports.

01:54:33.170 --> 01:54:38.110
And in general, for example, the substantial

01:54:38.120 --> 01:54:39.670
direction of the negotiations,

01:54:39.680 --> 01:54:41.290
the negotiations on agricultural issues

01:54:41.930 --> 01:54:45.410
came to the fact that in general, the

01:54:45.420 --> 01:54:49.530
position of Russia has not yet been

01:54:49.540 --> 01:54:52.250
recognized, the parties do not

01:54:52.260 --> 01:54:55.170
agree to accept the demand or

01:54:55.180 --> 01:54:57.810
the offer that Russia made for negotiations.

01:54:57.820 --> 01:54:58.670


01:54:58.850 --> 01:55:02.250
Russia proposes to fix the amount

01:55:02.260 --> 01:55:04.130
of support for our agriculture

01:55:07.180 --> 01:55:12.910
for the period 1993-1995.

01:55:12.920 --> 01:55:18.410
The amount of support will

01:55:18.420 --> 01:55:23.830
be $9.5 billion a year, but it

01:55:23.840 --> 01:55:26.970
would seem that this is not

01:55:26.980 --> 01:55:28.870
as much as the EU’s investments

01:55:28.880 --> 01:55:35.330
in its negotiating countries

01:55:35.340 --> 01:55:37.890
as the normal level of

01:55:37.900 --> 01:55:40.990
protectionist

01:55:41.000 --> 01:55:43.670
protection in the form

01:55:43.680 --> 01:55:46.450
of state subsidies

01:55:46.460 --> 01:55:48.230
for agriculture, export

01:55:48.240 --> 01:55:52.070
or national production economy.

01:55:53.230 --> 01:55:57.030
Moreover, the allowed amount of domestic

01:55:57.040 --> 01:56:00.670
state support of the agricultural sector,

01:56:00.680 --> 01:56:02.770
it does not, of course, apply to

01:56:02.780 --> 01:56:05.350
all types of agricultural products,

01:56:05.360 --> 01:56:07.330
but only to a certain list of the

01:56:07.340 --> 01:56:09.690
so-called yellow basket.

01:56:09.710 --> 01:56:12.170
This list includes agricultural

01:56:12.180 --> 01:56:12.990
products for which

01:56:13.000 --> 01:56:16.130
the World Trade Organization

01:56:16.140 --> 01:56:18.270
demands a reduction

01:56:18.280 --> 01:56:19.770
in protectionism.

01:56:19.780 --> 01:56:21.670


01:56:24.420 --> 01:56:26.640
The next block is the

01:56:26.650 --> 01:56:30.560
access to the service market.

01:56:31.040 --> 01:56:34.260
This is primarily financial

01:56:35.360 --> 01:56:38.620
services and energy

01:56:39.100 --> 01:56:40.740
services.

01:56:41.260 --> 01:56:45.140
And in this respect, of course, the

01:56:45.600 --> 01:56:48.280
struggle is due to the fact that

01:56:48.290 --> 01:56:51.520
restricting access to the service market

01:56:51.530 --> 01:56:55.900
is lobbied by our financial groups.

01:56:56.040 --> 01:56:59.160
And they prove that access to the

01:56:59.170 --> 01:57:00.920
financial market, which is not

01:57:00.930 --> 01:57:03.040
yet so sustainable, they think

01:57:03.440 --> 01:57:04.980
should be limited.

01:57:05.180 --> 01:57:06.500
Consequently, these problems

01:57:06.510 --> 01:57:09.700
are being solved during the negotiations.

01:57:09.710 --> 01:57:10.460


01:57:11.660 --> 01:57:13.720
The next sector is not only

01:57:13.730 --> 01:57:15.760
financial, but also energy.

01:57:18.020 --> 01:57:19.720
And here India advocates for access

01:57:19.730 --> 01:57:21.920
to individuals.

01:57:22.040 --> 01:57:23.600
India, Canada and Switzerland

01:57:23.610 --> 01:57:26.540
are advocating for individuals’ access

01:57:26.550 --> 01:57:30.760
to the Russian market

01:57:30.770 --> 01:57:33.120
in certain sectors of financial and

01:57:33.130 --> 01:57:35.380
energy services.

01:57:35.520 --> 01:57:38.180
In principle, the negotiators concluded

01:57:38.190 --> 01:57:41.440
that Russia agreed to open

01:57:41.450 --> 01:57:45.200
115 services sectors out of

01:57:45.210 --> 01:57:49.080
the 150 sectors listed by

01:57:49.090 --> 01:57:53.000
the World Trade Organization.

01:57:53.060 --> 01:57:56.980
But it puts forward requirements

01:57:57.380 --> 01:58:00.860
that involve tightening the working

01:58:00.870 --> 01:58:03.600
conditions of foreign service

01:58:03.610 --> 01:58:08.140
providers in the Russian market.

01:58:08.540 --> 01:58:12.260
And the next block, the last block,

01:58:12.660 --> 01:58:15.340
concerning the negotiation process,

01:58:15.480 --> 01:58:17.820
is negotiations on systemic issues.

01:58:17.960 --> 01:58:19.320
This is primarily

01:58:19.330 --> 01:58:21.040
the Russian law.

01:58:21.400 --> 01:58:25.500
Three blocks of questions are raised.

01:58:25.540 --> 01:58:26.540
The first.

01:58:26.580 --> 01:58:27.800
The Russian legislation, the

01:58:27.810 --> 01:58:31.840
requirements of the WTO in the field

01:58:31.850 --> 01:58:34.240
of application of sanitary and phytosanitary

01:58:34.250 --> 01:58:35.680
measures.

01:58:36.120 --> 01:58:37.840
Mostly, we have raised these questions

01:58:37.850 --> 01:58:39.700
with you already.

01:58:40.060 --> 01:58:42.060
This includes not only the various

01:58:42.070 --> 01:58:44.200
tariff quotas for meat, but also,

01:58:44.210 --> 01:58:46.960
as the WTO working group believes,

01:58:46.970 --> 01:58:49.340
excessive requirements for alcohol

01:58:49.350 --> 01:58:52.160
and pharmaceuticals.

01:58:52.260 --> 01:58:54.440
As you understand, the country that is being

01:58:54.450 --> 01:58:55.960
targeted is Georgia, and

01:58:55.970 --> 01:58:58.560
the country that is interested is India.

01:58:59.000 --> 01:59:05.300
The next direction is the use

01:59:05.310 --> 01:59:09.000
of some elements of state

01:59:09.010 --> 01:59:10.040
regulation in the sphere

01:59:10.050 --> 01:59:11.640
of foreign economic

01:59:11.650 --> 01:59:13.760
activity, which, again, does

01:59:14.200 --> 01:59:15.560
not meet the requirements

01:59:15.570 --> 01:59:17.280
and standards of the

01:59:17.290 --> 01:59:19.500
World Trade Organization.

01:59:19.780 --> 01:59:21.940
The last block of requirements on

01:59:21.950 --> 01:59:24.060
systemic issues of change of the

01:59:24.070 --> 01:59:28.220
legal system of Russia is called the WTO+.

01:59:28.230 --> 01:59:30.360
In principle, of course, Russia may

01:59:30.370 --> 01:59:31.680
not pay attention to them because

01:59:31.860 --> 01:59:34.520
they are not within the jurisdiction

01:59:34.530 --> 01:59:37.960
of the World Trade Organization.

01:59:38.580 --> 01:59:40.240
They are related to government procurement

01:59:40.250 --> 01:59:43.000
of civil aviation equipment.

01:59:43.600 --> 01:59:45.940
However, in order to eliminate possible

01:59:45.950 --> 01:59:48.740
conflicts and subsequent problems

01:59:48.750 --> 01:59:49.840
with the situation in foreign

01:59:49.850 --> 01:59:52.040
trade flows, these negotiations

01:59:52.050 --> 01:59:55.020
also take place.

01:59:56.060 --> 01:59:58.360
What other requirements do WTO member

01:59:58.370 --> 02:00:00.340
countries make to Russia in the

02:00:00.350 --> 02:00:02.860
framework of mutual agreements?

02:00:03.020 --> 02:00:05.380
This is the abolition of national

02:00:05.390 --> 02:00:07.680
components of investment projects.

02:00:07.690 --> 02:00:11.460
For now, it was assumed that when

02:00:11.470 --> 02:00:15.060
direct investments are made

02:00:16.710 --> 02:00:19.440
in the Russian market,

02:00:19.450 --> 02:00:22.100
the property belonging to

02:00:22.110 --> 02:00:23.780
domestic producers, the same

02:00:23.790 --> 02:00:25.500
national component, should

02:00:25.510 --> 02:00:27.480
also be included in this

02:00:27.490 --> 02:00:28.840
investment process.

02:00:29.960 --> 02:00:32.220
The next requirement is to ensure

02:00:32.230 --> 02:00:33.860
compliance with the requirements

02:00:33.870 --> 02:00:35.540
of the WTO, the applicable tariff

02:00:35.550 --> 02:00:37.400
quotas.

02:00:37.440 --> 02:00:39.040
This applies to agricultural

02:00:39.050 --> 02:00:41.140
agreements.

02:00:41.620 --> 02:00:44.600
This requirement involves

02:00:44.610 --> 02:00:45.960
such agreements that

02:00:45.970 --> 02:00:47.600
reduce their use.

02:00:48.540 --> 02:00:51.940
The next requirement is

02:00:51.950 --> 02:00:53.940
the organization of transactions

02:00:53.950 --> 02:00:55.220
of sale by state trade enterprises

02:00:55.230 --> 02:00:59.680
on a measureable basis.

02:00:59.900 --> 02:01:02.460
And the most important requirement is not

02:01:02.470 --> 02:01:06.200
to discriminate against foreign companies in participating

02:01:06.210 --> 02:01:08.640
in these transactions.

02:01:09.360 --> 02:01:11.820
This component is due to the

02:01:11.830 --> 02:01:13.980
fact that in the developed

02:01:13.990 --> 02:01:15.820
countries, the state

02:01:15.830 --> 02:01:18.500
primarily distributes

02:01:18.510 --> 02:01:22.680
state orders among domestic producers.

02:01:23.440 --> 02:01:26.020
But within the framework of these

02:01:26.030 --> 02:01:28.160
negotiations it is assumed that a consensus

02:01:28.170 --> 02:01:30.380
will be developed on the video,

02:01:30.500 --> 02:01:32.920
which will allow foreign companies

02:01:32.930 --> 02:01:34.960
to participate in more

02:01:34.970 --> 02:01:37.300
in government procurement

02:01:37.310 --> 02:01:39.400
programs.

02:01:39.520 --> 02:01:41.600
And the last essential

02:01:41.610 --> 02:01:43.000
requirement, put forward

02:01:43.010 --> 02:01:44.540
by the participants of the World

02:01:44.550 --> 02:01:46.820
Trade Organization, is the question

02:01:46.830 --> 02:01:52.660
of dual education on energy

02:01:53.420 --> 02:01:56.420
developed hard position,

02:01:56.540 --> 02:01:59.200
showing that we all, however,

02:01:59.210 --> 02:02:01.160
our energy goods, energy

02:02:01.240 --> 02:02:04.400
donors in certain volumes

02:02:04.410 --> 02:02:06.820
and at certain stable

02:02:06.830 --> 02:02:08.680
prices must first of all

02:02:08.690 --> 02:02:11.160
provide national demand

02:02:11.170 --> 02:02:13.640
of national producers.

02:02:14.980 --> 02:02:17.260
Now we will consider the last question

02:02:17.270 --> 02:02:20.420
of our lecture, concerning

02:02:20.430 --> 02:02:23.360
the readiness of the Russian

02:02:23.370 --> 02:02:24.820
market of Russian producers

02:02:24.830 --> 02:02:26.500
to join the WTO.

02:02:26.900 --> 02:02:29.180
On the one hand, Russian producers

02:02:29.190 --> 02:02:31.540
were protected from foreign flow of

02:02:31.550 --> 02:02:35.420
goods and services at the expense

02:02:35.430 --> 02:02:38.460
of the currency component almost

02:02:38.470 --> 02:02:42.980
in the period after the 1998 crisis.

02:02:43.400 --> 02:02:45.220
We have been aware of the situation

02:02:45.230 --> 02:02:47.620
in international economic relations

02:02:47.630 --> 02:02:50.360
where the exchange rate

02:02:50.370 --> 02:02:51.880
can act as a protectionist

02:02:51.890 --> 02:02:53.580
barrier.

02:02:54.000 --> 02:02:55.760
If the ruble is weak enough,

02:02:55.770 --> 02:02:58.260
it means that you can buy a

02:02:58.940 --> 02:03:01.400
smaller amount of dollars

02:03:01.410 --> 02:03:03.480
or euros for this ruble and,

02:03:03.490 --> 02:03:07.060
accordingly, a smaller

02:03:07.070 --> 02:03:10.000
amount of goods for imports.

02:03:10.010 --> 02:03:16.920
By 2001, the protectionism

02:03:16.930 --> 02:03:20.720
was exhausted.

02:03:20.780 --> 02:03:22.940
From this point of view, starting from

02:03:22.950 --> 02:03:25.420
2001, pay attention to the scheme, the

02:03:25.430 --> 02:03:26.480
schedule.

02:03:29.040 --> 02:03:31.640
The Russian manufacturer is in

02:03:31.650 --> 02:03:35.660
a situation of normal competitiveness.

02:03:36.580 --> 02:03:39.420
And the competition of imports from

02:03:39.430 --> 02:03:41.640
far abroad in this case has increased.

02:03:41.900 --> 02:03:43.360
This is not a new revelation

02:03:43.370 --> 02:03:45.840
for the Russian manufacturers.

02:03:47.220 --> 02:03:50.600
The Russian ruble is stillining

02:03:50.610 --> 02:03:52.700
stability and a certain

02:03:52.710 --> 02:03:56.380
pace of growth.

02:03:56.560 --> 02:03:58.800
This is all dependent on the

02:03:58.810 --> 02:04:01.020
central bank’s monetary policy.

02:04:01.260 --> 02:04:03.880
To what extent the central bank will decide

02:04:04.040 --> 02:04:06.940
it is acceptable for the Russian economy

02:04:06.950 --> 02:04:09.820
to deliberately intervene to reduce

02:04:09.830 --> 02:04:12.040
the currency rate of the ruble.

02:04:12.480 --> 02:04:15.620
Such an automatic mechanism,

02:04:15.630 --> 02:04:19.540
which was associated with

02:04:19.550 --> 02:04:22.500
a weak national ruble, is

02:04:22.510 --> 02:04:24.920
now exhausted.

02:04:24.930 --> 02:04:28.240
For the past five to six years, Russian

02:04:28.250 --> 02:04:31.620
manufacturers have been forced

02:04:31.630 --> 02:04:34.020
to take this into account.

02:04:36.360 --> 02:04:39.500
Russia’s tariffs on imports of

02:04:39.510 --> 02:04:41.480
agricultural products.

02:04:42.560 --> 02:04:45.740
In general, despite the fact

02:04:45.750 --> 02:04:48.680
that countries in the Conciliation

02:04:48.690 --> 02:04:53.120
Group demand some protectionist

02:04:53.130 --> 02:04:55.020
restrictions on agriculture,

02:04:55.030 --> 02:04:58.640
our tariffs are quite comparable

02:04:58.650 --> 02:05:00.540
to the restrictions

02:05:00.550 --> 02:05:03.380
currently in force in the territory

02:05:03.390 --> 02:05:05.540
of developed and developing

02:05:05.550 --> 02:05:07.520
countries.

02:05:08.320 --> 02:05:10.680
In developing countries,

02:05:10.780 --> 02:05:13.600
tariffs on agricultural

02:05:13.610 --> 02:05:15.260
imports are almost

02:05:15.270 --> 02:05:20.180
19%, and in such a large

02:05:20.190 --> 02:05:23.280
export economy as

02:05:23.290 --> 02:05:26.920
China, even 40%.

02:05:26.930 --> 02:05:29.880
In countries with transitional economies,

02:05:29.890 --> 02:05:33.160
this percentage is quite high and

02:05:33.170 --> 02:05:36.840
reaches about 16%.

02:05:36.850 --> 02:05:40.420
In developed countries, the level

02:05:40.430 --> 02:05:42.960
of protection of the national

02:05:42.970 --> 02:05:43.680
agricultural market

02:05:43.690 --> 02:05:46.060
is strong enough and, as you know,

02:05:46.070 --> 02:05:48.000
this is the main problem in negotiations

02:05:48.010 --> 02:05:49.800
between the EU and the United

02:05:49.810 --> 02:05:51.600
States, negotiations between

02:05:51.610 --> 02:05:54.580
the EU and developing countries.

02:05:54.740 --> 02:05:56.960
The EU has raised

02:05:56.970 --> 02:05:59.080
the protectionist protection

02:05:59.090 --> 02:06:01.620
in agriculture

02:06:01.630 --> 02:06:05.320
to 43.4%.

02:06:05.330 --> 02:06:08.080
In other words, there is a prohibitive

02:06:08.260 --> 02:06:11.440
level of tariffs.

02:06:12.740 --> 02:06:15.360
And based on these figures, we

02:06:15.370 --> 02:06:17.300
can say that our domestic agriculture

02:06:17.310 --> 02:06:19.080
and agricultural producers

02:06:19.090 --> 02:06:20.680
already operate within the framework

02:06:20.690 --> 02:06:23.080
of a sufficiently liberalized

02:06:23.090 --> 02:06:24.940
market for agricultural

02:06:24.950 --> 02:06:26.560
products.

02:06:26.880 --> 02:06:28.880
Therefore, the entry into

02:06:28.890 --> 02:06:30.560
the WTO whileining this

02:06:30.570 --> 02:06:32.980
level of protection for a transitional

02:06:32.990 --> 02:06:34.740
period, and even a decrease

02:06:34.750 --> 02:06:36.980
at a certain stage of this

02:06:36.990 --> 02:06:40.240
level, will not bring

02:06:40.250 --> 02:06:42.000
some unexpected outcome

02:06:42.010 --> 02:06:44.140
for agricultural producers.

02:06:44.900 --> 02:06:46.560
Pay attention to the slide,

02:06:46.740 --> 02:06:48.540
which illustrates the actual level

02:06:48.550 --> 02:06:52.160
of the import tariff.

02:06:52.170 --> 02:06:55.760
If we consider that the so-called

02:06:55.770 --> 02:06:58.460
weighted average rate of the import

02:06:58.470 --> 02:06:59.960
tariff is usually calculated in

02:06:59.970 --> 02:07:01.740
international debates and calculations,

02:07:01.750 --> 02:07:04.740
then by 2000, gradually decreasing,

02:07:04.750 --> 02:07:06.520
it reached an average of 2.5% in

02:07:06.530 --> 02:07:09.020
our country.

02:07:09.030 --> 02:07:11.480
Of course, this average is quite

02:07:11.490 --> 02:07:14.280
conditional, because it is calculated

02:07:14.290 --> 02:07:16.280
as a kind of average temperature

02:07:16.290 --> 02:07:17.940
for the hospital.

02:07:18.040 --> 02:07:20.680
One has a high temperature,

02:07:20.690 --> 02:07:22.860
the other is already

02:07:22.870 --> 02:07:24.080
cold.

02:07:24.380 --> 02:07:26.660
So, the weighted average rate

02:07:26.670 --> 02:07:28.560
is, I repeat again, now

02:07:28.570 --> 02:07:31.020
already by 2000, and now is

02:07:31.030 --> 02:07:34.500
still slightly below 12.5%.

02:07:34.510 --> 02:07:36.440
But an effective import

02:07:36.450 --> 02:07:38.660
tariff rate implies that we

02:07:38.860 --> 02:07:43.680
also take into account the shadow

02:07:43.690 --> 02:07:46.840
economy flows and other negative

02:07:46.850 --> 02:07:49.500
factors that lower the

02:07:50.100 --> 02:07:53.220
protectionist protection of

02:07:53.230 --> 02:07:55.600
the existing tariff.

02:07:55.620 --> 02:07:58.180
In this case, the

02:07:58.190 --> 02:08:00.300
effective rate of the import

02:08:00.310 --> 02:08:02.520
tariff is only about

02:08:02.530 --> 02:08:04.800
9%.

02:08:04.810 --> 02:08:08.560
Thus, the Russian market has already

02:08:08.570 --> 02:08:12.380
become accustomed to working in fairly

02:08:12.390 --> 02:08:14.360
tough conditions of competitive struggle

02:08:14.370 --> 02:08:16.080
with imports.

02:08:17.440 --> 02:08:20.300
The Russian proposals from the

02:08:20.310 --> 02:08:21.540
Russian delegation at

02:08:21.550 --> 02:08:25.500
the talks include expanding the

02:08:25.510 --> 02:08:29.280
corridor of protectionist rates

02:08:29.290 --> 02:08:31.140
and fixing the initial and

02:08:31.150 --> 02:08:33.680
final level of the related tariff

02:08:33.690 --> 02:08:35.220
bond, i.e. the upper and lower

02:08:35.230 --> 02:08:37.320
limit of the tariff,

02:08:37.330 --> 02:08:40.300
on industrial goods at the level

02:08:40.310 --> 02:08:47.020
of 14.3% to 9.8%, against

02:08:47.030 --> 02:08:52.780
the real level of 9.7% of the

02:08:52.790 --> 02:08:54.960
average tariff.

02:08:56.900 --> 02:09:00.640
What are the real factors

02:09:00.650 --> 02:09:02.600
of open economy?

02:09:02.840 --> 02:09:04.900
Of course, these are factors

02:09:04.910 --> 02:09:08.100
that are contrary to the normal

02:09:08.110 --> 02:09:10.580
operation of economic policy that

02:09:10.590 --> 02:09:14.820
is developed and in line with our legislation.

02:09:15.960 --> 02:09:20.200
First, on the one hand, these

02:09:20.210 --> 02:09:22.980
are such negative factors as

02:09:22.990 --> 02:09:26.000
the existence of gray schemes,

02:09:26.010 --> 02:09:28.980
when goods produced and

02:09:28.990 --> 02:09:30.940
designed for lower income

02:09:30.950 --> 02:09:32.360
of the population, oriented

02:09:32.440 --> 02:09:33.880
to some third developing countries,

02:09:33.890 --> 02:09:35.760
fall on the Russian

02:09:35.770 --> 02:09:36.780
market.

02:09:36.940 --> 02:09:39.220
Accordingly, they are essentially

02:09:39.230 --> 02:09:41.040
sold and offered under dumping

02:09:41.050 --> 02:09:45.020
schemes in relation to our goods.

02:09:45.100 --> 02:09:47.480
On the other hand, importers have

02:09:47.490 --> 02:09:50.460
serious schemes of tax optimization,

02:09:50.470 --> 02:09:52.840
which also lowers the price

02:09:52.850 --> 02:09:56.400
level of imported goods.

02:09:56.900 --> 02:09:59.260
The last negative component is the

02:09:59.270 --> 02:10:02.980
boat imports, which have recently

02:10:02.990 --> 02:10:04.060
been somewhat reduced, as

02:10:04.070 --> 02:10:08.180
competition in the Russian market,

02:10:08.190 --> 02:10:10.740
the growth of Russian population's

02:10:12.620 --> 02:10:15.100
income and the increase in the

02:10:15.110 --> 02:10:17.620
level of product quality requirements

02:10:17.630 --> 02:10:19.680
lead to the fact that gradually

02:10:19.690 --> 02:10:21.400
boat imports are collapsing

02:10:21.410 --> 02:10:23.700
and becoming more organized

02:10:23.710 --> 02:10:25.980
at the level of small and

02:10:25.990 --> 02:10:28.200
medium-sized importers.

02:10:28.760 --> 02:10:30.760
The next factor, which is no longer related

02:10:30.770 --> 02:10:32.320
to the shadow economy and is in principle

02:10:32.330 --> 02:10:34.880
subject to possible regulation by

02:10:34.890 --> 02:10:36.060
the government in the person

02:10:36.070 --> 02:10:38.700
of the Central Bank, is the rise

02:10:38.710 --> 02:10:40.380
of the ruble.

02:10:40.390 --> 02:10:43.400
As I said, a stronger and more stable

02:10:43.410 --> 02:10:45.540
ruble, but with a tendency

02:10:45.550 --> 02:10:47.720
to rise, usually restricts

02:10:47.730 --> 02:10:50.560
exports and increases imports.

02:10:51.260 --> 02:10:54.960
This factor has been working

02:10:54.970 --> 02:10:57.720
for a year, at least since

02:10:57.730 --> 02:10:59.380
2002.

02:10:59.960 --> 02:11:02.520
Russian manufacturers

02:11:02.530 --> 02:11:04.660
have also been used

02:11:04.670 --> 02:11:07.440
to this.

02:11:14.240 --> 02:11:18.060
According to the calculation

02:11:18.070 --> 02:11:21.620
of independent organizations, for

02:11:21.630 --> 02:11:24.740
six months of 2006 gray

02:11:24.750 --> 02:11:26.960
imports were quite serious,

02:11:28.440 --> 02:11:33.340
reaching $ 18 billion.

02:11:34.160 --> 02:11:40.440
However, this type of imports

02:11:40.450 --> 02:11:45.340
may decrease.

02:11:45.680 --> 02:11:45.740
Why is?

02:11:45.800 --> 02:11:48.920
Because if in 2005 the gray circuits

02:11:48.930 --> 02:11:52.480
covered a large range of products,

02:11:52.490 --> 02:11:54.340
the development of modern legislation

02:11:54.350 --> 02:11:56.500
and its adaptation to the

02:11:56.510 --> 02:11:58.280
WTO rules leads to the fact

02:11:58.290 --> 02:11:59.840
that gray imports are slightly

02:11:59.850 --> 02:12:05.420
reduced from 47% to 32%.

02:12:05.430 --> 02:12:07.940
The central bank, however, has

02:12:07.950 --> 02:12:12.200
lower figures, twice as low.

02:12:12.210 --> 02:12:15.000
But in this case, we will consider that

02:12:15.100 --> 02:12:16.600
the truth is somewhere in the middle

02:12:16.610 --> 02:12:18.600
between the expert assessment

02:12:18.610 --> 02:12:20.840
of specialists and the calculations

02:12:20.850 --> 02:12:21.940
of the Central Bank.

02:12:22.000 --> 02:12:24.740
Well, the last thing I would like to

02:12:24.750 --> 02:12:27.920
draw your attention to is that based

02:12:27.930 --> 02:12:31.200
on the previous slide scheme, we have

02:12:31.210 --> 02:12:33.620
in general already developed and introduced

02:12:33.630 --> 02:12:38.140
a fairly low level of average tariff

02:12:38.150 --> 02:12:40.080
in the Russian economy for a number

02:12:40.090 --> 02:12:41.860
of years, which covers

02:12:41.870 --> 02:12:44.800
about 50% of the products.

02:12:45.780 --> 02:12:52.380
Thus, we have solved the urgent and important

02:12:52.390 --> 02:12:55.540
problems related to Russia’s

02:12:55.550 --> 02:12:57.480
accession to the WTO.